      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(queue): persist followup queues across gateway restarts",
        "body": "## Problem\n\nWhen the gateway process restarts (npm update, crash, systemd restart), any\nmessages that arrived while an agent turn was in progress are silently lost.\nThe followup queue lives only in process memory — there is no recovery path.\n\nThis is particularly noticeable on channels that serialize messages (e.g.\nTelegram in queue mode): a message received during an active turn is queued\nfor delivery, then gone if the gateway restarts before that turn completes.\n\n## Solution\n\nAdd a JSON persistence layer for the `FOLLOWUP_QUEUES` global map.\n\n### New file: `src/auto-reply/reply/queue/persist.ts`\n\n- `persistFollowupQueues()` — serializes all non-empty queue entries to\n  `<stateDir>/live-chat-followup-queues.json`. Respects `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR`\n  via the existing `resolveStateDir()` utility. State file is deleted when all\n  queues drain to empty.\n- `restoreFollowupQueues()` — reads the state file at module init and repopulates\n  `FOLLOWUP_QUEUES` before any enqueue or drain fires.\n- `PersistedFollowupRun` — a `Pick<FollowupRun, ...>` type that explicitly\n  excludes runtime-only, non-serializable fields: `abortSignal`,\n  `currentTurnContext`, `deliveryCorrelations`, `queuedLifecycle`. These are\n  transient and must not survive a restart.\n\n### Mutation hooks\n\n`persistFollowupQueues()` is called after every state-changing operation:\n\n| Site | File |\n|---|---|\n| `enqueueFollowupRun` — after `items.push` | `enqueue.ts` |\n| Drain `finally` block — both empty-queue delete and reschedule branches | `drain.ts` |\n| `clearFollowupQueue` — after `FOLLOWUP_QUEUES.delete` | `state.ts` |\n| `refreshQueuedFollowupSession` — after the run-rewrite loop | `state.ts` |\n\n### Tests\n\n`persist.test.ts` covers:\n- State file written when queue has items\n- State file deleted when all queues are empty\n- Full round-trip: enqueue → persist → simulated restart → restore → verify prompt + routing fields\n- Runtime-only `abortSignal` field not present after restore\n- No-op when state file does not exist\n- Malformed entries (non-array items, null key) are skipped\n\n## Notes\n\n- The `draining: false` invariant is enforced on restore — any in-flight drain\n  that was interrupted is restarted by the normal drain scheduler on next enqueue.\n- `summarySources` (contains `FollowupRun` objects, not serializable) is reset to\n  `[]` on restore. `summaryLines` (plain strings) is persisted and restored.\n- No schema migration needed for v1; unrecognized fields are ignored on restore.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Queued followup messages received during an active agent turn survive a gateway restart and redeliver exactly once. This head (`3ca1f5a78`) also persists `originatingReplyToId` and `inputProvenance` so restored runs keep reply-target context.\n- Real environment tested: Local dev checkout on Linux (`jewseppi/openclaw`, branch `feat/queue-followup-persistence`), Node 24, real temp state dir via `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR`, real on-disk `live-chat-followup-queues.json` I/O (no in-memory mocks for persist/restore).\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n  ```bash\n  cd openclaw\n  pnpm exec vitest run \\\n    src/auto-reply/reply/queue.followup-restart-roundtrip.test.ts \\\n    src/auto-reply/reply/queue/persist.test.ts\n  ```\n- Evidence after fix: Terminal output (live module + real filesystem):\n  ```\n  RUN  v4.1.7 /home/joseph/dev/openclaw\n\n   Test Files  2 passed (2)\n        Tests  19 passed (19)\n   Duration  2.18s\n\n  Covered behaviors on head 3ca1f5a78:\n  - Telegram-routed followup queued mid-turn → persisted to disk → simulated gateway restart → restore → exactly-once redelivery → no replay after second restart\n  - originatingReplyToId + inputProvenance round-trip through persist+restore\n  - state file mode 0o600, atomic write, auth profile selectors preserved, secret-bearing config stripped\n  ```\n- Observed result after fix: After simulated restart, restored queue items retain prompt, Telegram routing, reply target, and input provenance; drain delivers the restored prompt once; post-drain persistence prevents replay on a second restart.\n- What was not tested: Full live native Telegram desktop capture (Mantis run failed on shared QA infra). Contributor-side live Telegram E2E remains blocked by gateway/session serialization constraints documented in prior PR comments.\n\n### Storage note (ClawSweeper P1)\n\nThis PR intentionally uses a named v1 sidecar (`live-chat-followup-queues.json`) for crash-recovery of in-memory followup queues. A SQLite/shared-state migration is a larger follow-up; this patch keeps the artifact private (0o600), atomic, and minimal (allowlisted fields only). Happy to move to shared-state DB if maintainers prefer that shape before merge.\n\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
